      Problem

  Prove by induction that the $i$th Fibonacci number satisfies the equality
\begin{equation}
  F_i= \frac{\phi^i-\hat{\phi}^i}{\sqrt{5}},
\end{equation}
where $\phi$ is the golden ratio and $\hat{\phi}$​ is its conjugate.(two roots of the equation）
\begin{equation}
  x^2 = x + 1
\end{equation}


